{
  "verses": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "text": [
        "The Sayings for King Lemuel"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "1",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "These are the words of King Lemuel—the burden that his mother taught him:"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "2",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "genealogy",
          "text": "What shall I say, O my son? What, O son of my womb?\nWhat, O son of my vows?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "3",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Do not spend your strength on womenor your vigor on those who ruin kings."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "4",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "It is not for kings, O Lemuel, it is not for kings to drink wine,\nor for rulers to crave strong drink,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "5",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "lest they drink and forget what is decreed, depriving all the oppressed of justice."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "6",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Give strong drink to one who is perishing, and wine to the bitter in soul."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "7",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Let him drink and forget his poverty, and remember his misery no more."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "8",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Open your mouth for those with no voice, for the cause of all the dispossessed."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "9",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Open your mouth, judge righteously, and defend the cause of the poor and needy."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "text": [
        "The Virtues of a Noble Woman"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "10",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "A wife of noble character, who can find? She is far more precious than rubies."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "11",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The heart of her husband trusts in her, and he lacks nothing of value."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "12",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "She brings him good and not harmall the days of her life."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "13",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "She selects wool and flax and works with eager hands."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "14",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "She is like the merchant ships, bringing her food from afar."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "15",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "She rises while it is still nightto provide food for her household\nand portions for her maidservants."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "16",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "She appraises a field and buys it; from her earnings she plants a vineyard."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "17",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "She girds herself with strength and shows that her arms are strong."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "18",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "She sees that her gain is good, and her lamp is not extinguished at night."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "19",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "She stretches out her hands to the distaff and grasps the spindle with her fingers."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "20",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "She opens her arms to the poor and reaches out her hands to the needy."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "21",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "When it snows, she has no fear for her household, for they are all clothed in scarlet."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "22",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "She makes coverings for her bed; her clothing is fine linen and purple."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "23",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Her husband is known at the city gate, where he sits among the elders of the land."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "24",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "She makes linen garments and sells them; she delivers sashes to the merchants."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "25",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Strength and honor are her clothing, and she can laugh at the days to come."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "26",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "She opens her mouth with wisdom, and faithful instruction is on her tongue."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "27",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "She watches over the affairs of her household and does not eat the bread of idleness."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "28",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Her children rise up and call her blessed; her husband praises her as well:"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "29",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "Many daughters have done noble things, but you surpass them all!",
          "speaker": "Unknown"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "30",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Charm is deceptive and beauty is fleeting, but a woman who fears the LORD is to be praised."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "31",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Give her the fruit of her hands, and let her works praise her at the gates."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    }
  ]
}